# Development Setup

## Cache Cleanup

If you encounter issues with the development server or need to clear cached files, use the following commands:

### Quick Cache Cleanup
```bash
npm run del:cache
```
This command will:
1. Kill any processes running on port 4321
2. Remove `.astro` and `node_modules/.vite` cache directories

### Manual Cache Cleanup
If you prefer to run the commands manually:
```bash
# Kill processes on port 4321
npm run port:kill:4321

# Clean cache directories
npm run clean:cache
```

### PowerShell Command (Alternative)
You can also run the PowerShell command directly:
```powershell
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .astro, node_modules\.vite -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
```

## Content Auto-Puller

The content auto-puller script (`scripts/content-autopull.mjs`) now automatically:
- Detects the repository root using `git rev-parse --show-toplevel`
- Changes to the repository root directory before running git commands
- Handles errors gracefully with proper cleanup
- Reduces log verbosity for better development experience

The script will exit gracefully if not run from within a git repository.
